quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,Does he not know that when the graves are emptied out
  100,10,and the heart´s contents are brought into the open
  100,11,that Day their Lord will certainly be aware of them
  101,1,The Crashing Blow
  101,2,What is the Crashing Blow
  101,3,What will convey to you what the Crashing Blow is
  101,4,It is the Day when mankind will be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains like tufts of coloured wool
  101,6,As for him whose balance is heavy
  101,7,he will have a most pleasant life
  101,8,But as for him whose balance is light
  101,9,his motherland is Hawiya
  101,10,And what will convey to you what that is
  101,11,A raging Fire
  102,1,Fierce competition for this world distracted you
  102,2,until you went down to the graves
  102,3,"No indeed, you will soon know"
  102,4,"Again no indeed, you will soon know"
  102,5,"No indeed, if you only knew with the Knowledge of Certainty"
  102,6,you will certainly see the Blazing Fire
  102,7,Then you will certainly see it with the Eye of Certainty
  102,8,Then you will be asked that Day about the pleasures you enjoyed
  103,1,By the Late Afternoon
  103,2,truly man is in loss —
  103,3,except for those who have iman and do right actions and urge each other to the truth and urge each other to steadfastness
  104,1,Woe to every faultfinding backbiter
  104,2,who has amassed wealth and hoarded it
  104,3,He thinks his wealth will make him live for ever
  104,4,No indeed! He will be flung into the Shatterer
  104,5,And what will convey to you what the Shatterer is
  104,6,The kindled Fire of Allah
  104,7,reaching right into the heart
  104,8,It is sealed in above them
  104,9,in towering columns
  105,1,Do you not see what your Lord did with the Companions of the Elephant
  105,2,Did He not bring all their schemes to nothing
  105,3,unleashing upon them flock after flock of birds
  105,4,bombarding them with stones of hard-baked clay
  105,5,making them like stripped wheat-stalks eaten bare
  106,1,In acknowledgment of the established tradition of Quraysh
  106,2,their tradition of the winter and summer caravans
  106,3,so let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,who has preserved them from hunger and secured them from fear
  107,1,Have you seen him who denies the deen
  107,2,He is the one who harshly rebuffs the orphan
  107,3,and does not urge the feeding of the poor
  107,4,So woe to those who do salat
  107,5,and are forgetful of their salat
  107,6,those who show off
  107,7,and deny help to others
  108,1,Truly We have given you the Great Abundance
  108,2,So pray to your Lord and sacrifice
  108,3,It is the one who hates you who is cut off without an heir
  109,1,"Say: ´Kafirun"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,and you do not worship what I worship
  109,4,Nor will I worship what you worship
  109,5,nor will you worship what I worship
  109,6,You have your deen and I have my deen.´
  110,1,When Allah´s help and victory have arrived
  110,2,and you have seen people entering Allah´s deen in droves
  110,3,then glorify your Lord´s praise and ask His forgiveness. He is the Ever-Returning
  111,1,Ruin to the hands of Abu Lahab and ruin to him
  111,2,His wealth has not helped him nor anything he has earned
  111,3,He will burn in a Flaming Fire
  111,4,"And so will his wife, the firewood-carrier"
  111,5,with a rope of twisted fibre round her neck
  112,1,"Say: ´He is Allah, Absolute Oneness"
  112,2,"Allah, the Everlasting Sustainer of all"
  112,3,He has not given birth and was not born
  112,4,And no one is comparable to Him.´
  113,1,"Say: ´I seek refuge with the Lord of Daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of what He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the darkness when it gathers
  113,4,and from the evil of women who blow on knots
  113,5,and from the evil of an envier when he envies.´
  114,1,"Say: ´I seek refuge with the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,the King of mankind
  114,3,the God of mankind
  114,4,from the evil of the insidious whisperer
  114,5,who whispers in people´s breasts
  114,6,and comes from the jinn and from mankind.´